cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

The paper proposes two discriminative learning frameworks for Gaussian Bayesian networks (GBN) for neuroimaging based brain network analysis. This involves learning from high dimensional continuous data, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the focus is on learning discriminative parameters of GBNs, which is a machine learning task, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the use of neuroimaging data and network analysis.
